Perkins Family to reduce distributions . Perkins Family Restaurants LP said Monday that it plans to reduce or eliminate its cash distributions as a result of a change in federal income tax law that will require most publicly traded limited partnerships to be taxed as a corporation beginning January 1 , 1998 . The company said that it is now advising partners that with the requirement of tax payments beginning in 1998 , it plans to reduce the cash distributions by at least the amount of the taxes and perhaps even eliminate the distributions . 
